				                <div>Hello Jeanne,<br />
<br />
Thanks for the question and sorry that you can't yet get into your WordPress dashboard.  The main reason is that you just signed up and registered a brand new domain name.  When you register a new domain name, it needs up to 24 hours before it is recognized on the internet.   This is known as <a href="http://www.inmotionhosting.com/support/domain-names/dns-nameserver-changes/domain-names-dns-changes" target="new">DNS propagation</a>.  The servers on the internet are still being updated with your domain name - it doesn't happen instantaneously.    So, please give it a little more time and then you will be able to see your WordPress dashboard.  <br />
<br />
If you cannot wait, you would need to change your WordPress settings to use the temporary URL.  We do have instructions on <a href="http://www.inmotionhosting.com/support/edu/wordpress/wordpress-introduction/installing-wordpress-using-your-temporary-url" target="new">how to install Wordpress to a temporary URL</a>, but I would recommend this only if you're on a tight deadline.  Once the DNS propagation period passes, in order to use your original domain name you would need to reverse the changes you made to use the WordPress site with the temp URL.   <br />
<br />
I hope this helps to clarify the issue for you!  Please let us know if you require any further assistance.<br />
<br />
Kindest regards,<br />
Arnel C.</div>
